Abstract = {{We derive an implicit-explicit (IMEX) formalism for the
   three-dimensional (3D) Euler equations that allow a unified
   representation of various nonhydrostatic flow regimes, including cloud
   resolving and mesoscale (flow in a 3D Cartesian domain) as well as
   global regimes (flow in spherical geometries). This general IMEX
   formalism admits numerous types of methods including single-stage
   multistep methods (e.g., Adams methods and backward difference formulas)
