   polynomials defined on the triangles and tetrahedra, while the equations
   themselves are satisfied in a discontinuous Galerkin form with the
   boundary conditions being enforced weakly through a penalty term.
   Accuracy, stability, and convergence of the semidiscrete approximation
   to Maxwell's equations is established rigorously and bounds on the
   growth of the global divergence error are provided. Concerns related to
